organizations theory and management home general information contact info calendar course materials announcements ms&e 180 organizations theory and management fall 2011 the purpose of this course is to increase your ability to understand and improve the organizations within which you will work it is a course in applied behavioral science by this i mean that we will review some fundamental behavioral science concepts and illustrate how they can be effectively used in organizations although the emphasis is on high technology and manufacturing organizations the course material applies to organizations in general we will consider individuals groups and organizations time tuesday thursday 10 00 11 50 am location thornton room 110 enrollment restricted enrollment preference to ms &e majors graduate and co term students see ms &e 280 no freshmen download syllabus
